                            <comment id="17457083" author="gupta.nikhil0007" created="Fri, 10 Dec 2021 11:55:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Similar fix for HBASE: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-26557&quot; title=&quot;log4j2 has a critical RCE vulnerability&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-26557&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-26557&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; log4j2 has a critical RCE vulnerability - ASF JIRA (apache.org)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17457558" author="kgyrtkirk" created="Sat, 11 Dec 2021 08:00:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not so thrilled - as it seems to me that this is not exploitable above java8u191 - which was released in 2018&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.veracode.com/blog/security-news/urgent-analysis-and-remediation-guidance-log4j-zero-day-rce-cve-2021-44228&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.veracode.com/blog/security-news/urgent-analysis-and-remediation-guidance-log4j-zero-day-rce-cve-2021-44228&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;


    Log4j version &#8211; all 2.x versions before 2.15.0 (released today, Friday, December 10, 2021) are affected
    JVM version - &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; lower than:
        Java 6 &#8211; 6u212
        Java 7 &#8211; 7u202
        Java 8 &#8211; 8u192
        Java 11 - 11.0.2
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so people running ancient java runtime and a vulnerable log4j are out of luck...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17457596" author="jasonmadam" created="Sat, 11 Dec 2021 11:53:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Zoltan,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The latest Java versions are most likely still vulnerable to RCE. &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/608?s=09#issuecomment-991396409&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/logging-log4j2/pull/608?s=09#issuecomment-991396409&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17457982" author="sankarh" created="Sun, 12 Dec 2021 16:24:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=gupta.nikhil0007&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;gupta.nikhil0007&quot;&gt;gupta.nikhil0007&lt;/a&gt; for the contribution! PR merged to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17460399" author="hao.duan" created="Thu, 16 Dec 2021 04:08:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; the &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;hive1. X&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; version is not affected&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17460457" author="elukey" created="Thu, 16 Dec 2021 07:38:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi everybody! I am trying to patch Hive 2.3.x for Apache Bigtop, and I am wondering if a backport to branch-2.3 is planned/in-scope or not &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17460489" author="brahmareddy" created="Thu, 16 Dec 2021 08:30:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Linking the branch-3 PR which is raised by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ngangam&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ngangam&quot;&gt;ngangam&lt;/a&gt; ..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17461573" author="renato_de_melo@yahoo.com.br" created="Fri, 17 Dec 2021 17:16:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is the version 3.1.1 also affected?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I scanned it and I got the following result:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;*&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Found CVE-2021-44228 vulnerability in /opt/hive/lib/log4j-core-2.10.0.jar, log4j 2.10.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17461801" author="brahmareddy" created="Sat, 18 Dec 2021 07:06:17 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&#160;Is the version 3.1.1 also affected?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Yes. As this CVE effects &lt;b&gt;2.0 &amp;lt;= Apache log4j2 &amp;lt;= 2.14.1.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17481883" author="JIRAUSER284183" created="Tue, 25 Jan 2022 15:11:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi team,&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can see this issue was resolved but Hive 3.1.2 available &lt;a href=&quot;https://archive.apache.org/dist/hive/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; is still including an old version of log4j, do you plan to update the current binary package or release a new version of Hive with the new Log4j&apos;s libraries?&lt;/p&gt;

